The following snippet:

```TypeScript
module A.C {
    export interface Z {
    }
}

module A.B.C {
    export class W implements A.C.Z {
    }
}
```
Produces the following declarations (using â€“declaration)
```TypeScript
module A.C {
    interface Z {
    }
}
module A.B.C {
    class W implements C.Z {
    }
}
```
Basically, the interface A.C.Z is incorrectly emitted as C.Z.
